01:04.480 --> 01:07.610
Many strange tales
are told of this Jungle...

01:07.776 --> 01:09.653
but none so strange...

01:09.820 --> 01:13.074
as the tale of the cub we call Mowgli.

02:25.270 --> 02:27.898
You must be the very
worst wolf I've ever seen.

02:28.398 --> 02:31.322
Yeah, but if that branch didn't break,
I would've made it.

02:31.860 --> 02:34.329
Crossing upwind,
breaking from your numbers.

02:34.738 --> 02:35.864
If you can't learn to run with the Pack...

02:36.031 --> 02:37.499
one of these days,
you'll be someone's dinner.

02:37.658 --> 02:38.830
- How'd we do?
- Not Mowgli, again.

02:38.992 --> 02:41.541
- He's never gonna make the Council.
- Let's go!

02:41.703 --> 02:43.421
Race you to the top!

02:44.164 --> 02:45.757
It was higher ground.

02:45.916 --> 02:48.089
Wolves don't hide in trees.

02:48.251 --> 02:49.423
I can't keep up with them, Bagheera.

02:49.836 --> 02:51.588
I tried. I just picked the wrong tree.

02:51.755 --> 02:53.098
It was a dead tree.

02:53.548 --> 02:55.596
How was I supposed to know it was dead?

02:55.759 --> 02:56.885
It had a fig vine.

02:57.052 --> 03:00.977
Any tree girdled by a creeper
is either dead or close to it.

03:01.139 --> 03:04.143
- These are things a wolf must know.
- Yeah.

03:04.559 --> 03:07.403
But if the branch didn't break,
I would've made it.

03:07.979 --> 03:12.276
I realise you weren't born a wolf,
but couldn't you at least act like one?

03:16.446 --> 03:19.666
When I found him, many years ago...

03:20.325 --> 03:23.625
he was just an infant,
abandoned in the woods.

03:23.787 --> 03:25.289
Get the deer!

03:26.456 --> 03:28.584
If he was going to survive...

03:29.167 --> 03:31.295
I knew he needed a people.

03:31.461 --> 03:33.259
A people to protect him.

03:34.297 --> 03:37.221
That's why I entrusted him to the wolves.

03:40.595 --> 03:42.268
Look well, wolves.

03:43.807 --> 03:47.027
Akela was a just and noble leader.

03:47.561 --> 03:50.531
He allowed Mowgli to dwell
among them, all those years.

03:53.316 --> 03:56.661
The trouble was, wolves grew so fast...

03:57.154 --> 03:58.371
and Mowgli...

03:58.530 --> 04:01.158
let's just say he liked to take his time.

04:01.324 --> 04:02.496
Mowgli, pick me up high!

04:03.034 --> 04:05.207
- My turn!
- Stop. Not now.

04:05.370 --> 04:07.543
It was Raksha who raised him.

04:07.706 --> 04:09.708
She was the only mother he ever knew

04:10.167 --> 04:12.761
- Come on, let's play!
- I don't feel like playing, Gray.

04:12.919 --> 04:14.967
Come on, you're my brother.
You have to play with me.

04:15.130 --> 04:17.007
Let's go chase some mice.

04:19.301 --> 04:20.974
How did it go?

04:21.636 --> 04:23.138
Caught me again.

04:24.097 --> 04:25.815
If it's meant to be...

04:25.974 --> 04:27.897
it will be.

04:28.560 --> 04:30.187
Let me hear the Law.

04:30.854 --> 04:35.322
"This is the Law of the Jungle,
as old and as true as the sky.

04:35.859 --> 04:37.907
"The Wolf that keeps it will prosper...

04:38.069 --> 04:40.822
"but the Wolf that breaks it will die.

04:40.989 --> 04:43.538
"Like the creeper that girdles
the tree trunk...

04:43.700 --> 04:46.044
"the Law runneth over and back.

04:46.203 --> 04:48.752
"For the strength of the Pack
is the Wolf...

04:48.914 --> 04:52.384
"and the strength of the Wolf
is the Pack."

05:20.904 --> 05:22.906
Soon, the rain ceased to fall

05:22.989 --> 05:24.866
and the dry season arrived.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.298
Heat crept through the Jungle...

05:32.457 --> 05:35.252
turning it yellow, then brown...

05:35.418 --> 05:36.795
then black.

05:39.214 --> 05:40.682
But that year...

05:40.841 --> 05:43.845
was the driest season
that anyone could remember.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.183
Even the mohwa didn't flower.

05:51.977 --> 05:53.069
My leaf.

05:54.729 --> 05:56.652
This is mine. Mine, mine, mine.

05:56.815 --> 05:59.238
There's a rock. That's mud. That's mud.

05:59.401 --> 06:00.869
There's a rock. That's my rock.

06:01.027 --> 06:02.700
That's my rock. Nobody touches my rock.

06:02.863 --> 06:05.286
There's another rock.
Two rocks. Three rocks.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.291
Peace Rock? Peace Rock!

06:08.660 --> 06:10.913
It's the Truce! The Water Truce!

06:11.913 --> 06:14.132
It's the Water Truce!

06:15.417 --> 06:17.090
It had been many, many years

06:17.168 --> 06:19.170
since the Peace Rock was revealed...

06:19.921 --> 06:22.174
and the Water Truce was called.

06:29.639 --> 06:31.808
Hunting at the riverbank
was now forbidden...

06:31.975 --> 06:35.650
because, by Law of the Jungle,
drinking comes before eating.

06:35.812 --> 06:38.907
So, you could come to the Peace Rock,
on a day like this...

06:39.065 --> 06:42.160
and find all people side-by-side.

06:53.788 --> 06:54.789
Don't forget.

06:54.873 --> 06:55.920
No hunting.

06:55.999 --> 06:57.000
Playing only.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.593
Playing, only. I got it, ami.

06:59.085 --> 07:02.805
And remember, not everyone here
has seen a man-cub in the Jungle before.

07:02.964 --> 07:04.341
So, behave yourself.

07:04.799 --> 07:06.392
Okay, can I go now?

07:06.551 --> 07:07.768
Take the pups with you.

07:08.553 --> 07:09.896
Wait for me!

07:10.513 --> 07:11.605
Come on, Gray!

07:12.974 --> 07:13.975
Oh, take a look at this guy.

07:14.935 --> 07:15.936
Excuse me.

07:16.019 --> 07:17.771
Sorry.

07:17.979 --> 07:20.073
- He's walking on two legs.
- Don't stare.

07:20.231 --> 07:21.483
Hey, look. A wild boar.

07:21.650 --> 07:24.028
- And a rhino.
- And a mongoose.

07:24.194 --> 07:25.195
Everybody's here.

07:25.946 --> 07:27.664
Is that a peacock?

07:28.365 --> 07:29.867
- Ooh, a stick!
- Oh, that's my stick.

07:30.033 --> 07:31.501
- I like this stick.
- Seriously, that's my stick.

07:31.660 --> 07:32.707
- This is my stick.
- No, that's my stick!

07:32.869 --> 07:34.371
- Let go of my stick!
- It's a Water Truce!

07:34.537 --> 07:36.710
It's a Water Truce!

07:36.831 --> 07:37.878
Sorry.

07:38.333 --> 07:40.461
My bad! It's involuntary.

07:41.419 --> 07:42.591
I could pee on it.

07:42.754 --> 07:44.301
Watch yourself, please.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.091
Dad, what is that?

07:46.257 --> 07:47.884
I think that's a man-cub.

07:48.051 --> 07:50.053
What's a man-cub doing here?

07:51.638 --> 07:53.231
Whoa. Don't forget the Truce.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.063
I know the Law, bucks.

08:03.108 --> 08:04.451
What is that?

08:17.414 --> 08:18.916
- Weird.
- That's weird.

08:20.458 --> 08:21.459
Mowgli.

08:25.088 --> 08:27.432
What was the rule about your tricks?

08:28.591 --> 08:30.593
It's not the wolf way.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.433
No more tricks.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.274
Chin up, little one.

08:36.433 --> 08:38.025
We'll make you a fine wolf, yet.

08:40.437 --> 08:42.110
What about me? Am I gonna be a fine wolf?

08:42.272 --> 08:43.398
Look at me howl!

08:46.860 --> 08:48.737
In some packs, the runt gets eaten.

08:49.112 --> 08:50.113
Oh...

09:05.670 --> 09:07.138
Mowgli, behind me.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.557
Don't leave my side.

09:57.847 --> 10:02.227
Everyone comes to Peace Rock.
So many smells to catch up on.

10:08.399 --> 10:09.616
But, um...

10:12.946 --> 10:14.539
I can't help but notice...

10:14.948 --> 10:18.202
there's this strange odour today.

10:20.203 --> 10:23.707
What is it, this scent that I'm on?

10:26.042 --> 10:27.294
I almost...

10:28.086 --> 10:30.555
I almost think it was some kind of...

10:31.422 --> 10:32.423
man-cub.

10:34.884 --> 10:38.104
Mowgli belongs to my Pack, Shere Khan.

10:38.555 --> 10:39.556
Mowgli?

10:40.223 --> 10:42.317
They've given it a name.

10:43.226 --> 10:47.902
When was it we came to adopt
man into the Jungle?

10:48.314 --> 10:49.907
He's just a cub.

10:50.358 --> 10:54.363
Does my face not remind you
of what a grown man can do?

10:57.907 --> 11:02.455
Shift your hunting ground for a few years
and everyone forgets how the Law works.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.668
Well, let me remind you.

11:05.290 --> 11:10.428
A man-cub becomes man...
and man is forbidden!

11:12.255 --> 11:14.599
- What do you know about Law?
- Raksha.

11:14.757 --> 11:17.226
Hunting for pleasure. Killing for power.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.930
You've never known Law. The cub is mine!

11:20.638 --> 11:21.639
Mine to me.

11:21.764 --> 11:23.892
So, go back to where you came from,
you burned beast!

11:27.687 --> 11:30.782
The tiger knows who rules
this part of the Jungle.

11:31.232 --> 11:33.781
I'm sure he doesn't mean to come here
and make threats.

11:34.611 --> 11:37.490
Especially during a Water Truce.

11:45.580 --> 11:49.960
No, I'm deeply respectful of these Laws
that keep us safe.

11:50.627 --> 11:52.504
So, here's my promise.

11:53.296 --> 11:55.173
Nothing lasts forever.

11:56.299 --> 12:00.270
The rains will return
and the river will rise.

12:00.678 --> 12:04.148
And when this rock disappears,
that Truce will end.

12:05.642 --> 12:08.145
You want to protect him, fine.

12:08.645 --> 12:14.197
But ask yourselves,
how many lives is a man-cub worth?

12:28.706 --> 12:30.504
How many lives?

12:32.835 --> 12:34.837
Who could answer that question?

13:04.242 --> 13:06.210
- The rain!
- Rain!

13:06.369 --> 13:07.370
- Rain!
- The rain!

13:08.830 --> 13:11.424
Keep it dry, keep it dry, keep it dry.

13:12.041 --> 13:14.339
These quills get stuck on everything!

13:17.046 --> 13:22.393
When the rains returned, it was
a question the Council had to face.

13:48.119 --> 13:52.586
They deliberated and they argued...
for many days.

13:57.879 --> 13:59.881
What do you think they're talking about?

14:01.924 --> 14:04.768
No one had ever come
between the Pack before.

14:06.137 --> 14:08.435
But Shere Khan's threat...

14:08.598 --> 14:10.600
was not to be ignored.

14:18.775 --> 14:21.403
Mowgli, you're not supposed
to go up there!

14:28.951 --> 14:30.294
He's got to go.

14:31.996 --> 14:32.997
Look at the skies.

14:33.956 --> 14:36.300
Shere Khan may be heading here
as we speak.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.051
Please!

14:41.005 --> 14:42.552
I'm leaving.

14:45.802 --> 14:47.349
I don't want to see anyone get hurt.

14:47.845 --> 14:49.518
Mowgli, go back to the den!

14:50.014 --> 14:51.311
A man-cub belongs with man.

14:51.808 --> 14:53.276
We raised him as one of our own!

14:53.601 --> 14:56.104
- He'll have the boy, either way.
- Akela.

14:58.481 --> 14:59.949
Maybe I can be of help.

15:00.108 --> 15:01.485
The boy's right.

15:01.651 --> 15:03.528
Maybe it's time he found another people.

15:03.986 --> 15:06.364
- No.
- I'm the one who brought him to you.

15:06.531 --> 15:08.659
And now I'll return him
to where he belongs.

15:08.991 --> 15:10.117
I won't let you.

15:10.535 --> 15:11.661
He's my cub!

15:12.078 --> 15:13.170
We knew this day would come.

15:13.496 --> 15:15.590
We are the only family he's ever known!

15:15.748 --> 15:16.840
Raksha.

15:18.626 --> 15:21.220
It's the only place he'll be safe.

15:25.842 --> 15:27.139
It's okay, ami.

15:27.301 --> 15:28.848
I won't go far.

15:29.512 --> 15:31.685
I'll come back and visit.

15:33.266 --> 15:35.439
Never forget this...

15:36.269 --> 15:38.192
You're mine.

15:38.354 --> 15:39.901
Mine to me.

15:40.606 --> 15:44.156
No matter where you go,
or what they may call you...

15:44.318 --> 15:45.740
you will always be...

15:46.195 --> 15:47.447
my son.

16:25.401 --> 16:26.869
I wish I could tell you...

16:27.028 --> 16:29.577
that the wolves
could've fought Shere Khan.

16:31.407 --> 16:33.580
But this is not that kind of a tale.

16:35.870 --> 16:37.747
The turtles like me.

16:37.914 --> 16:39.757
Maybe the crocodiles.

16:40.249 --> 16:41.375
What about the rhinos?

16:41.542 --> 16:43.419
They always let me hang around.

16:44.754 --> 16:46.722
Of course, the rhinos sleep standing up.

16:48.424 --> 16:50.267
I don't think I'd be very good at that.

16:50.426 --> 16:52.724
It's either the turtles or the crocodiles.

16:53.179 --> 16:54.601
Which one do you think is better?

16:54.764 --> 16:56.016
Neither.

16:56.182 --> 16:57.855
What do you mean?

16:58.017 --> 17:00.236
I'm bringing you to the man village.

17:01.604 --> 17:02.605
What?

17:03.272 --> 17:05.569
Bagheera, I don't know man.

17:05.733 --> 17:06.858
You will.

17:08.861 --> 17:10.454
You always said we're not supposed

17:10.570 --> 17:12.618
to go near a man village.

17:12.781 --> 17:14.625
That was different.

17:14.784 --> 17:16.377
Why is it different?

17:16.786 --> 17:18.413
You always said, "Stay away
from the man village...

17:18.579 --> 17:20.080
"because you might fall in a trap...

17:20.540 --> 17:22.759
"or get eaten,
or get hurt by flying rocks."

17:22.916 --> 17:24.589
I know what I said.

17:29.799 --> 17:32.723
Whoa. Elephants.

17:33.177 --> 17:35.305
- Bow your head.
- Why?

17:35.471 --> 17:37.473
Show them respect.

17:37.974 --> 17:40.443
The elephants created this Jungle.

17:40.601 --> 17:43.980
Where they made furrows
with their tusks, the rivers ran.

17:44.146 --> 17:45.898
Where they blew with
their trunks, the leaves fell.

17:46.983 --> 17:49.327
They made all that belongs.

17:49.485 --> 17:52.784
The mountains, the trees,
the birds in the trees.

17:52.947 --> 17:54.494
But they did not make you.

17:55.449 --> 17:57.247
That is why you must go.

18:25.771 --> 18:27.023
What if I live with the nilgai?

18:27.106 --> 18:28.107
No.

18:28.691 --> 18:29.817
Or the mongoose?

18:29.984 --> 18:31.531
This is not a discussion.

18:31.694 --> 18:32.991
But this is my home!

18:33.070 --> 18:34.538
I don't even know what man's like.

18:34.697 --> 18:35.949
You'll learn.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.367
But I wanna stay in the Jungle.

18:37.783 --> 18:39.080
Why do I have to go there?

18:39.243 --> 18:41.416
Because the Jungle
is no longer safe for you.

18:41.579 --> 18:42.580
You're being hunted...

18:42.997 --> 18:44.044
by a tiger.

18:44.206 --> 18:46.083
Only man can protect you now.

18:46.167 --> 18:47.168
Whoa!

18:48.461 --> 18:51.214
This isn't fair.
You're not giving me a choice.

18:51.380 --> 18:52.973
There's a lot of stuff
you're not telling me, too.

18:53.132 --> 18:54.634
Don't think I didn't notice.

18:54.800 --> 18:56.518
You say you're taking me
where I came from...

18:56.677 --> 18:58.145
but you found me in the Jungle.

18:58.304 --> 19:00.682
Are you bringing me back
to the Jungle? No.

19:00.848 --> 19:03.643
Why are you bringing me to the man
village if you found me in the Jungle?

19:03.809 --> 19:05.732
And why does the tiger hate me so much?

19:05.895 --> 19:07.818
Does he know me?
Sure seems like he knows me.

19:07.938 --> 19:08.939
Down.

19:09.982 --> 19:12.826
What? Now we have to bow
to the buffalo, too?

19:12.985 --> 19:14.862
Listen to me. This is not a game.

19:15.029 --> 19:16.906
You're gonna run to that ravine.

19:17.281 --> 19:18.908
What are you talking about?

19:19.367 --> 19:20.835
Go to the north,
where the sky glows at night.

19:20.993 --> 19:21.994
I'll find you on that path.

19:22.411 --> 19:24.379
Bagheera, I'm not taking one
more step until you tell me...

19:51.774 --> 19:53.117
Run, Mowgli!

19:54.944 --> 19:55.945
Run!

21:29.872 --> 21:31.249
Gray, what's wrong?

21:31.415 --> 21:33.383
Why don't you come outside and play?

21:35.044 --> 21:36.136
What is that?

21:40.424 --> 21:42.097
Why did he have to leave?

21:42.259 --> 21:43.260
Gray.

21:43.427 --> 21:47.307
We could've protected him.
We shouldn't have let him go.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.225
I miss him, too.

21:49.725 --> 21:52.353
What's important is, he's safe now.

22:00.277 --> 22:01.779
Get inside.

22:47.283 --> 22:49.957
I suppose you know why I've come.

22:52.788 --> 22:54.916
The man-cub has left the Jungle.

22:59.503 --> 23:01.221
I thought I made myself clear.

23:01.380 --> 23:03.553
I wanted him turned over to me.

23:04.550 --> 23:06.473
We no longer harbour him.

23:07.011 --> 23:09.309
He has left the Pack.

23:10.180 --> 23:13.024
And where, may I ask, has he gone?

23:17.771 --> 23:19.523
He's with his own kind now.

23:21.817 --> 23:24.070
So, the man-cub has left the Jungle.

23:24.862 --> 23:26.159
That's right.

23:26.739 --> 23:28.912
You and I no longer have a quarrel.

23:29.074 --> 23:30.997
And, most importantly...

23:31.160 --> 23:32.503
we have peace.

23:39.084 --> 23:41.086
I guess it's done, then.

23:42.504 --> 23:44.381
Unless I can draw him...

23:44.840 --> 23:45.887
back out!

23:46.383 --> 23:47.851
Akela!

23:51.221 --> 23:53.064
Have I got your attention now?

23:53.515 --> 23:56.018
I didn't want it to be this way.

23:56.185 --> 23:58.358
I made it so simple.

23:58.520 --> 24:02.150
All I asked for was one thing,
and you denied me!

24:03.067 --> 24:05.161
That ends now.

24:05.569 --> 24:07.196
Spread the word.

24:07.696 --> 24:11.121
Until I have the man-cub,
these hills are my hills.

24:11.283 --> 24:13.706
You did not respond to reason!

24:14.203 --> 24:15.921
So now, you will know fear.

27:05.707 --> 27:07.380
Bagheera?

28:48.018 --> 28:49.019
Hmm?

28:51.813 --> 28:53.235
Hey, there.

28:56.944 --> 28:58.366
Do you have a language?

29:02.324 --> 29:04.372
You're kind of cute, I guess.

29:05.994 --> 29:07.541
You want a bite?

29:09.456 --> 29:10.457
Come on.

29:10.791 --> 29:13.169
Come here. Come on, it's all right.

29:13.335 --> 29:14.632
Don't be afraid.

29:24.304 --> 29:25.681
Come on.

29:27.641 --> 29:29.359
Hey, those are mine!

29:33.105 --> 29:34.402
Hey, come back!

29:36.608 --> 29:38.201
Those are mine!

29:40.195 --> 29:41.492
Drop it!

29:57.921 --> 29:59.389
Hello?

30:16.898 --> 30:18.445
Who's out there?

30:18.900 --> 30:20.743
Hi, little cub.

30:21.737 --> 30:23.785
Oh, no. Don't be scared.

30:25.032 --> 30:26.750
I'm not gonna hurt you.

30:28.910 --> 30:32.915
I was just passing through.
I don't want any trouble.

30:33.081 --> 30:35.083
There's no trouble.

30:36.084 --> 30:37.961
Are you alone out here?

30:38.754 --> 30:40.597
Mmm. That's not good.

30:40.964 --> 30:43.433
We should never be alone.

30:44.426 --> 30:46.428
I'm waiting for a friend.

30:46.595 --> 30:48.438
He should be here soon.

30:49.931 --> 30:51.979
I can stay with you, until he gets here.

30:53.310 --> 30:55.278
Would that be all right?

30:58.440 --> 31:00.442
I'll keep you safe.

31:01.485 --> 31:04.455
Just you and me, sweet thing.

31:07.574 --> 31:09.076
Who are you?

31:11.828 --> 31:14.047
Kaa.

31:19.836 --> 31:22.259
Poor, sweet little cub.

31:23.131 --> 31:26.226
What are you doing so deep in the Jungle?

31:27.636 --> 31:29.309
This is my home.

31:29.971 --> 31:31.518
Don't you know what you are?

31:33.975 --> 31:35.977
I know what you are.

31:38.480 --> 31:40.858
I know where you came from.

31:41.817 --> 31:43.444
You do?

31:44.152 --> 31:45.495
Yes.

31:51.827 --> 31:54.501
Would you like to see?

31:57.791 --> 31:59.008
Yeah.

32:01.795 --> 32:04.514
Mostly, men stay in their village...

32:04.714 --> 32:07.217
far from the dark of the Jungle.

32:07.676 --> 32:09.053
But sometimes...

32:09.219 --> 32:10.721
they travel.

32:10.887 --> 32:12.855
And when they do...

32:13.014 --> 32:16.018
their caves breathe in the dark.

32:16.184 --> 32:17.686
They call it...

32:18.812 --> 32:21.531
the Red Flower.

32:30.657 --> 32:32.409
Man's creation.

32:33.410 --> 32:35.538
It brings warmth and light...

32:36.371 --> 32:39.045
and destruction to all that it touches.

32:43.336 --> 32:44.713
Who is that?

32:44.880 --> 32:47.975
The traveller, protecting his cub.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.833
Shere Khan ended
the man's life that night.

33:16.244 --> 33:20.249
But not before he was burned
by the Red Flower's touch.

33:20.832 --> 33:25.087
He ran so fast, he didn't
notice the cub he left behind.

33:35.305 --> 33:37.148
And that cub...

33:37.307 --> 33:38.433
was you.

34:03.083 --> 34:05.131
The panther found you.

34:16.679 --> 34:19.809
Oh, you poor, sweet thing.

34:22.185 --> 34:24.279
You want to stay in the Jungle?

34:29.150 --> 34:31.494
You can be with me, if you want.

34:32.529 --> 34:34.657
I'll keep you close.

34:36.116 --> 34:38.494
Let go of your fear, now.

34:41.161 --> 34:43.540
Trust...

34:43.831 --> 34:45.175
in me.

35:14.738 --> 35:15.739
Relax, kid.

35:15.905 --> 35:17.202
No need to get worked up. Okay?

35:17.741 --> 35:19.334
- Where am I?
- Uh...

35:20.368 --> 35:22.541
This is a cave. It's my cave.

35:24.664 --> 35:26.166
You don't remember what happened, do you?

35:26.708 --> 35:28.551
- No.
- I saved your life.

35:29.544 --> 35:31.592
Yeah, I snatched you
from the jaws of death.

35:31.755 --> 35:33.928
The coils of death, if you will.

35:34.090 --> 35:35.967
And lucky for you...

35:36.384 --> 35:38.227
your new favourite hero,
old Baloo, here...

35:38.386 --> 35:40.730
just happened to be passing by.

35:40.889 --> 35:41.890
Uh, no big deal.

35:42.223 --> 35:44.191
Just tell me this.

35:44.643 --> 35:45.940
Can you...

35:47.228 --> 35:48.571
climb?

35:50.398 --> 35:51.490
Yeah.

35:51.858 --> 35:54.737
Then let's quit wasting time
and get on with it.

35:55.195 --> 35:56.412
Get on with what?

35:56.905 --> 35:58.907
Payback, kid. Payback.

35:59.407 --> 36:02.035
What do you mean "payback"?
Payback for what?

36:03.995 --> 36:05.247
You owe me, kid.

36:05.413 --> 36:07.131
You owe me. You owe me.

36:07.290 --> 36:08.291
Slow down.

36:08.416 --> 36:10.214
- And you're gonna pay back.
- But, but...

36:10.377 --> 36:11.469
Because that's right.

36:11.586 --> 36:12.803
You're gonna do the right thing.

36:12.962 --> 36:13.963
That's the right thing to do.

36:14.130 --> 36:15.473
You're gonna pay me back,
because you owe me.

36:15.632 --> 36:16.724
You got it?

36:26.101 --> 36:27.444
Okay, here's our little task.

36:27.602 --> 36:29.604
You see that golden stuff,
dripping down there?

36:30.063 --> 36:31.406
That's called "honey."

36:31.773 --> 36:33.446
All you need to do, little one...

36:33.608 --> 36:35.076
for payback purposes...

36:35.235 --> 36:37.613
is to just shimmy on up there...

36:37.779 --> 36:40.328
and get me that thing up there
that's making that funny noise...

36:40.490 --> 36:41.992
and bring it back down.

36:44.285 --> 36:45.878
You're kidding me, right?

36:46.621 --> 36:48.419
No, not really.

36:48.957 --> 36:51.085
I can get killed going up there.

36:51.251 --> 36:52.468
Kid!

36:52.961 --> 36:55.089
Kid, kid, kid. Try to understand this.

36:55.588 --> 36:56.760
I'm a bear.

36:56.923 --> 36:59.472
It means that I have to eat my weight...

36:59.634 --> 37:00.681
every day...

37:00.844 --> 37:02.471
for hibernation purposes.

37:02.929 --> 37:07.396
I know I'm asking for a lot,
but I don't climb and you do.

37:08.184 --> 37:11.108
Look, I really need your help.
Winter's coming.

37:11.271 --> 37:13.273
You don't want me to go to sleep...

37:13.440 --> 37:15.283
and never wake up.

38:40.068 --> 38:42.070
There are a lot of bees up here.

38:42.403 --> 38:43.905
Yeah, some.

38:44.072 --> 38:46.370
But don't worry. These ones don't sting.

38:53.957 --> 38:55.129
Attaboy!

38:56.042 --> 38:57.419
Ow! I'm getting stung!

39:00.046 --> 39:01.719
Okay.

39:02.131 --> 39:05.635
I would've done this myself,
but I'm afraid of heights.

39:06.177 --> 39:07.269
Oh, boy. Here we go again.

39:07.762 --> 39:08.763
Why don't you mind your own business?

39:09.097 --> 39:10.098
You can do it!

39:10.265 --> 39:12.233
- He's just gonna run away.
- Not this one.

39:12.725 --> 39:14.147
As soon as the monkeys get
stung, they always run away.

39:14.519 --> 39:16.396
- He's not a monkey. A man-cub.
- What is he?

39:16.813 --> 39:18.690
A man-cub?
Yeah! Could you keep your voice down?

39:18.898 --> 39:20.024
I'm trying to concentrate.

39:20.525 --> 39:23.369
- Everything going A-okay up there?
- Ow!

39:24.070 --> 39:25.913
Oh, boy. Looks like you got another one.

39:26.281 --> 39:27.453
- Buzz off.
- It's a man-cub.

39:27.907 --> 39:28.954
- A man-cub?
- Yeah, it's a man-cub.

39:29.117 --> 39:31.415
- It's not a monkey?
- No, it's a man-cub!

39:32.078 --> 39:34.456
You have never been
a more endangered species...

39:34.622 --> 39:36.124
than you are at this moment.

39:36.499 --> 39:38.501
You're doing an amazing job!

39:38.793 --> 39:40.136
I'm getting stung!

39:40.628 --> 39:41.925
Oh, boy. Here we go again.

39:42.088 --> 39:43.806
- It's not a monkey, Fred.
- It's a man-cub.

39:43.965 --> 39:45.308
- A man-cub?
- Yeah, it's a man-cub.

39:45.466 --> 39:47.059
- Can you believe it?
- Are you sure?

39:47.552 --> 39:48.769
Would you please shut up?

39:49.137 --> 39:50.309
Hey, up there!

39:50.471 --> 39:52.644
Everything is going fantastically, I see.

39:54.642 --> 39:55.814
Ow!

39:56.853 --> 39:58.901
